     </m:msup>
   </m:mrow>
  </m:mfrac>
 </m:mfenced>
 <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mtext>22</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">×</m:mo><m:msup><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo><m:mn>7</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:msup><m:mspace width="0.25em"/></m:mrow><m:mtext> m</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mtext>122 nm</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{λ= left ( {  {m}  over  {1 "." "097" times "10" rSup { size 8{7} } } }  right ) left [ {  { \( 2 "." 1 \)  rSup { size 8{2} } }  over  {4 - 1} }  right ]=1 "." "22" times "10" rSup { size 8{ - 7} } " m"="122"" nm"} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> , which is UV radiation.</para></solution>
